author: Inside Edition
description: More allegations have surfaced in connection with the death of an 18-year-old cheerleader on a cruise ship. The father of Anna Kepner's former boyfriend claims Kepner's 16-year-old stepbrother, who is under suspicion in her death, was obsessed with her. Her funeral took place in Orlando Thursday. Inside Edition was told there is tension among family members and some have been told they were not welcome to the funeral. Kepner's biological mother spoke with Inside Edition.
title: Biological Mother of Anna Kepner Speaks Out In Exclusive Interview

author: Inside Edition
description: A woman who worked on New Jersey Republican congressman Jeff Van Drew's staff told police she was attacked by three men who hate President Donald Trump. Images show her body covered with slashed across her body. The woman has been identified as 26-year-old Natalie Greene. She's also a student at Rutgers Law School. Now, police say it was all a hoax. Authorities say Greene paid a body artist $500 to cut her body with a scalpel.
title: Former GOP Staffer Accused Of Faking Anti-Trump Attack

author: Inside Edition
description: Former presidents George W. Bush, Joe Biden and their wives Laura and Dr. Jill were in the front pew at Dick Cheney's funeral. Former vice presidents Al Gore, Dan Quayle, Kamala Harris and Mike Pence were also in attendance. President Donald Trump and Vice President JD Vance were not invited to the funeral. Trump and the Cheneys are foes. Last year, Dick Cheney announced he was voting for Kamala Harris. Meanwhile, Trump launched an attack on Jimmy Kimmel overnight.
title: Donald Trump And JD Vance Not Invited To Dick Cheney's Funeral

author: Inside Edition
description: A Jet Blue pilot died after eating a hamburger. The autopsy says Brian Waitzel died a "sudden unexplained death." His fate baffled his family as he seemed to be in perfect health. A year after the mysterious death, a team of doctors believe a tick bite made the 47-year-old pilot allergic to red meat and no one knew it. Waitzel was declared dead around seven hours after eating a hamburger. It's believed Waitzel was bitten when he was jogging at a state park in New Jersey.
title: Doctors Say A Tick Was Behind A Pilot's Mysterious Death

author: Inside Edition
description: One man's mission in life has been to fly like a bird. Peter Salzmann of Austria created a wingsuit to bring him closer to soaring the skies. The suit is designed with foil that he says helped him maintain altitude. Salzmann tested his creation in the Canary Islands. He says he was able to fly for more than two minutes without losing more than 200 meters of altitude. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Man Creates Wingsuit To Soar Like A Bird

author: Inside Edition
description: Would you believe New Yorkers are lining up for lunch of Venezuelan Chinese fried rice sold from the trunk of a car? Customers tell WCBS it's a unique experience. The cook behind the craze is Yony Hung, 22, a Chinese Venezuelan who wanted to share his unique culture with others. It's got a combination of ham, shrimp, pork, and chicken and is sold alongside eggrolls. Hungry people show up at whatever location he posts on social media. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: New Yorkers Lining Up For Venezuelan Chinese Food Sold From Trunk Of A Car

author: Inside Edition
description: New details are emerging in the mysterious death of 18-year-old Anna Kepner, who was found dead on a cruise ship. Court documents say Kepner's 16-year-old stepbrother is a suspect in the FBI investigation. Inside Edition spoke with Kepner's best friend, Genovisia Guerrero about the stunning development. Kepner was on the Carnival cruise ship with her father, stepmother, Shauntel, and two of the stepmother's children from a previous marriage. A criminal case may be initiated, authorities say.
title: Stepbrother Named Suspect After Teen Found Dead On Cruise: Filing
